[2026-04-30] Tool registry architecture (Phase 1)
================================================
Discussed with: Codex (codex exec, transcript /tmp/codex-discuss-tool-registry.md)
Outcome: Accepted Codex pushback in full.

Decisions:
- Location: packages/tool-registry (pnpm workspace package; no server runtime dep)
- Surface: CLI `pcl-tools` is the cross-language boundary; direct TS imports are private
- Execution context REQUIRED on every call: companyId, projectId, issueId|runId, actor, toolName, validated args (no bypass)
- Secrets: ~/.paperclip/tool-secrets.json (not in repo); keyed by company/source
- Telemetry: <workspace>/tool_calls.jsonl per project (separate from decisions.jsonl which stays for product artifacts); fields = ts, company, project, issue/run, tool, args-hash-or-redacted, status, duration_ms, cost_units, error_class
- Phase 1 endpoints (3, single auth surface): lingxing.factSku, lingxing.factOrders, toolCalls.search
- Killer use case: rewrite ONE close-loop script's lingxing data-access path to use `pcl-tools lingxing fact-{sku,orders}`. Do not touch its SP-API or Shopify calls. Target: scripts/eval/close-loop-ads.ts in EP workspace.
- Python scripts: subprocess-wrap (typed I/O validation), do NOT rewrite shopify_spider in Phase 1
- Deferred to Phase 2: HTTP routes, MCP server, SP-API/Shopify endpoints, brief→issue parser, DB-backed telemetry

