[2026-04-30 evening] Tool registry Phase 2 architecture
========================================================
Discussed with: Codex (transcript /tmp/codex-discuss-mcp-and-sources.md)
Outcome: Accepted all 5 pushbacks; cut scope from "MCP+3 sources" to "MCP+Shopify only".

Decisions:
- MCP wrap lives INSIDE packages/tool-registry (option A); add second bin `pcl-tools-mcp` next to `pcl-tools`. Do NOT extend packages/mcp-server (control-plane MCP separate from data MCP — different auth, blast radius, operator expectations).
- Add registry-level tool descriptor as canonical model: { id, description, inputSchema, outputSchema, source, readOnly, requiredSecrets, handler }. Derive BOTH CLI and MCP from it. CLI keeps existing kebab subcommand aliases for backward compat.
- MCP tool naming: dotted-namespace + camelCase (e.g. `lingxing.factSku`, `shopify.getProduct`). Per MCP spec 2025-06-18 — letters/digits/_-. allowed.
- Secrets schema: keep tool-secrets.json physically loose (Record<string,string>) but add per-source Zod schemas validated at context construction or first call. Never include secret-derived values in telemetry or argsHash.
- Standardize subprocess helper contract BEFORE adding new sources: JSON stdin/stdout, structured error envelope ({error, message}), explicit timeout (configurable per tool), stderr capture, no shell interpolation, version field in request payload, test fixtures for each helper.
- Phase 2 ships ONLY: registry metadata refactor + MCP server + subprocess contract + per-source secret schemas + Shopify read tools (getProduct, listProductsByCollection).
- Deferred to Phase 3: Meta Marketing API tools, Amazon SP-API tools. Reason: Shopify proves the non-lingxing subprocess pattern; Meta/SP-API have higher-risk dimensions (API versioning, auth shape, rate limits, pagination, marketplace scoping) that warrant the pattern be battle-tested first.

# 2026-05-07 — DingTalk bot 与 paperclip agent 平台关系
- 钉钉 bot (paperclip-dingtalk-bot/) 当前是平行的 mini agent 平台：自带 LLM dispatcher (tabcode/gpt-5.4) / system prompt / SQLite 会话记忆 / 工具调度。与 paperclip 的 issue-driven agent 系统业务平行，仅在 tool-registry / secrets / telemetry 层共享。**已知架构债，不立即修复。**
- 理想架构：bot 极薄 DingTalk 适配层，转发到 paperclip 的 Concierge agent。阻碍：paperclip server 没有同步 chat-with-agent endpoint（routes 全是 issue / approval / routine）。
- 触发迁移条件：用户出现高频 "bot ↔ paperclip 联动" 需求（如 bot 派 issue / 读 decisions / paperclip agent 推送钉钉），或多人维护双系统认知成本不可接受。
- 跟踪 spec: docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-07-everpretty-bot-future-roadmap.md
